            . I am a Police-serjeant. I took the prisoner at lslington, in consequence of information - he said he thought there must be some mistake, and he had no knowledge of this shop; I asked him about all the other baker's shops in lslington, and he knew them all but the prosecutor's.</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded distress.</p>
